=Description=

"DIYBio– do-it-yourself biology – is an organization based in the USA, which aim is “to help make biology a worthwhile pursuit for citizen scientists, amateur biologists, and DIY biological engineers who value openness and safety”. Their practices of biohacking are related to a 'democratization of science' they want to foster. Their growing community is organized around the project's website and a network of local groups."


